# AI Memory Index
# Format: MDL (Memory Description Language)
# This file is ALWAYS loaded (~200 tokens)

@meta: updated=2026-03-05 | version=1.0 | topics=auth,api,db,deploy

## STACK
runtime: Node 20.x + TypeScript 5.3
db: PostgreSQL 16 + Redis 7
framework: Express 4.x
orm: Prisma 5.x

## ARCH
auth: JWT | src/auth/jwt.ts | tokens(access:15m,refresh:7d) | oauth:Google,GitHub
api: REST+tRPC | src/api | validation:Zod | routes:src/api/routes/*.ts
db: Prisma | conn:src/db/client.ts | migrations:prisma/migrations
cache: Redis | client:src/cache/redis.ts | ttl:300s | keys:user:*,session:*
errors: AppError | src/errors/AppError.ts | never throw strings

## PATTERNS
config: Zod schemas in src/config/*.ts | env validation
tests: Vitest | colocated .test.ts | coverage>80%
logging: Winston | src/utils/logger.ts | levels:error,warn,info
validation: Zod | inline schemas | export types

## DECISIONS (critical)
- No ORMs in edge functions (use raw SQL)
- All dates in UTC, convert at display layer
- API versioning: /v1/, /v2/ in routes
- Soft deletes: deletedAt timestamp

## CURRENT (auto-prune:weekly)
2026-03-05: Refactoring auth → OAuth2 integration in progress
2026-03-01: BREAKING - User.role changed from string to enum
2026-02-28: Added rate limiting middleware (100req/15min)

## AVOID (known anti-patterns)
- ❌ Don't use any in TypeScript (use unknown)
- ❌ Don't store passwords unhashed
- ❌ Don't expose internal errors to client
- ❌ Don't use var (use const/let)

## TOPICS
Load these files on keyword match:
- auth.mdl → authentication, jwt, oauth, tokens, login, sessions
- api.mdl → routes, endpoints, tRPC, REST, validation
- db.mdl → database, prisma, migrations, queries, schema
- deploy.mdl → deployment, docker, ci/cd, environment
- perf.mdl → performance, caching, optimization, redis
- testing.mdl → tests, vitest, mocking, coverage
